            .</p>
               <p>ROBERT CHAPMAN. I <rs id="t18270913-296-viclabel1650" type="occupation">keep a public-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-296-victim2289 t18270913-296-viclabel1650"></join> in <placeName id="t18270913-296-crimeloc1651">Belton-street, Long-acre</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-296-crimeloc1651" type="placeName" value="Belton-street, Long-acre"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-296-crimeloc1651" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-296-off1648 t18270913-296-crimeloc1651"></join>. On the 8th of September, while I was out, my till was stolen from the bar; when I came home, the prisoner came in, and called for half-a-pint of porter - my wife charged him with it - he denied it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-296-person2290">
                  SOPHIA 
                  LYALL
               <interp inst="t18270913-296-person2290" type="surname" value="LYALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-296-person2290" type="given" value="SOPHIA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-296-person2290" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live opposite Chapman. I saw the prisoner and another go into the house and bring out a box, as I thought; it was between twelve and one o'clock - the other went in, and brought it out to the prisoner, who took it, and they went off together - I told a man, who went into the house and told the woman in the bar - I had seen the prisoner before, and believe him to be the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-296-person2291">
                  SUSANNAH 
                  HADLEY
               <interp inst="t18270913-296-person2291" type="surname" value="HADLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-296-person2291" type="given" value="SUSANNAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-296-person2291" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in Chapman's employ. I saw the prisoner and another at the door; about one o'clock I left the bar to get some water, and as I came back along the passage, I heard a noise - I went into the bar, and saw Lyall; I then missed the till.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-296-person2292">
                  JOHN 
                  TURNER
               <interp inst="t18270913-296-person2292" type="surname" value="TURNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-296-person2292" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-296-person2292" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I apprehended the prisoner a little after two o'clock - he promised to pay the money by instalments.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was at the door, a and man ran out, by me; I had some pears in my apron.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270913-296-verdict1652" type="verdictDescription">
